# Nova / Luna Core

## Mission

- Keep this project focused on Nova / Luna only.
- Do not mix it with Jarvis or any unrelated assistant/trading workflow.
- Nova is the male assistant.
- Luna is the female assistant.
- Keep the app phone-first, with smartwatch support treated as a later companion layer.
- Keep the system local-first and on-device as much as possible.
- Keep zero backend cost by default.
- Do not require paid APIs unless the user explicitly approves them.

## Project Direction

- Voice command, voice reply, task automation, and assistant personality are core features.
- Prefer practical, shippable improvements over speculative architecture.
- Do not introduce fake success states or pretend features are complete.
- Do not add hardcoded secrets, tokens, or hidden network dependencies.
- Prefer free and open-source tooling where possible.

## Documentation

- Keep reports and working notes in `docs/`.
- Update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` when architecture changes.
- Update `docs/WORK_PROCESS_REPORT.md` when the workflow or build process changes.
- Keep the docs honest about what is implemented now versus what is planned.

## Source Of Truth

- Cursor should read `AGENTS.md` first if it is available.
- Use the root instruction files to keep agent behavior aligned with the project mission.
